title: 6A_2D
source_name_ch1: hiPSC-derived beta like cells at Stage7
treatment_protocol_ch1: Different cell lins were differentiated in Aggrewell plates (3D), encapsulated in Alginate, or in 2D conditation respectively.
growth_protocol_ch1: The directed differentiation of hiPSCs to β-like cells was performed as previously described (7, 8). To reduce variability between different differentiations we performed the original differentiation in parallel in the same multiwell-plate for all conditions with the same batch of differentiation cocktail. At the end of Stage 5, 5.0 million cells were embedded in alginate beads, as previously described (13), 2.4 million cells were used to form cell aggregates (11) and approximately 5 million were kept in adherent culture. The beads, aggregates and planar cultures were differentiated until ST7 as previously described (7, 14).
extract_protocol_ch1: RNA from cell clusters were isolated using  Qiagen RNeasy kit. RNA from alginate capsules were snap freeze in the kit lysis buffer, without de-algination, RNA were then isolated by following the recommended process.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: The library preparation was done using the QIAseq UPX 3’ Transcriptome Kit (QIAGEN). A total of 10 ng (sample 1-7), 2.5 ng (sample 8-14) purified RNA was converted into cDNA NGS libraries. During reverse transcription, each sample was tagged with a unique ID, and each RNA molecule was tagged with a unique molecular index (UMI). The samples were then pooled into one tube for downstream processing. Quality control of the library preparation was performed using capillary electrophoresis (Agilent DNA 7500 Chip) and the libraries were quantified using qPCR.
data_processing: Raw data was de-multiplexed and FASTQ files for each sample were generated using the bcl2fastq2 software (Illumina inc.).
data_processing.1: The “Demultiplex QIAseq UPX 3’ reads” tool of the CLC Genomics Workbench 21.0.4 was used to demultiplex the raw sequencing reads according to the sample indices.
data_processing.2: The reads were then mapped to the Human genome GRCh38 and annotated using the ENSEMBL GRCh38 v. 98 gene annotation.
data_processing.4: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Matrix table with raw gene counts for every gene and every sample
contact_address: Dept of Pediatrics, Haukeland University Hospital
